==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skatol
<hw>Ska"tol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/<?/<?/, dung +
<ets>-ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A constituent of
human faeces formed in the small intestines as a product of the
putrefaction of albuminous matter. It is also found in reduced indigo.
Chemically it is methyl indol, <chform>C9H9N</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

